-> Steps to Generate and Use the Correct Service Account Credentials
Create a Service Account:

Go to the Google Cloud Console.
Navigate to IAM & Admin > Service Accounts.
Click Create Service Account.
Enter a name and description for the service account, then click Create.
Under "Grant this service account access to the project," choose the appropriate role (e.g., "Editor" or "Drive API Admin" for accessing Google Drive).
Click Continue and Done.
Generate a Key:

Once the service account is created, select it from the list.
Go to the Keys tab and click Add Key > Create New Key.
Choose the JSON key type and click Create.
A JSON file will be downloaded. This is the credentials file you need.
Use the Service Account Credentials:

Replace the existing credentials.json with the newly downloaded service account JSON file.

-> Steps to Generate and Use the OAuth 2.0 Credentials.
Go to the Google Cloud Console: Google Cloud Console.
Enable the Google Drive API for your project.
Navigate to APIs & Services > Credentials.
Create OAuth Credentials:
Click on Create Credentials and select OAuth 2.0 Client IDs.
Youâ€™ll need to configure the consent screen and provide the necessary details, such as application name and redirect URIs (where users will be redirected after authentication).
Download the OAuth 2.0 credentials file (usually named client_secret.json).